  "description": {
    "en-US": "Travel phrases for France with audio, designed for SNCF trains, hotel check-ins, cafe etiquette, boulangeries, museums, and everyday service questions.",
    "zh-CN": "法国旅行短语卡，围绕 SNCF 火车、酒店入住、咖啡馆礼貌表达、面包店、博物馆和日常服务沟通整理。"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en-US": "Built for France trips where SNCF station changes, hotel arrivals, cafe counters, and museum queues can all happen in one afternoon. These cards help when you want to open with bonjour, ask a short follow-up question, or show a phrase on screen instead of slowing the line down.",
    "zh-CN": "这套法国短语适合那种一天里会连续遇到 SNCF 火车换站、酒店入住、咖啡馆点单和博物馆排队的旅行节奏。想先说一声 bonjour，再补一句简短需求，或者不想让队伍停下来时，直接展示短语卡会更自然。"
  },
  "teaser": {
    "en-US": "Built for France rail travel, SNCF questions, cafe etiquette, hotel arrivals, and short museum or bakery requests.",
    "zh-CN": "适合法国铁路出行、SNCF 询问、咖啡馆礼貌表达、酒店入住和博物馆或面包店简短沟通。"
  },
  "travelTips": {
    "en-US": [
      "Start with bonjour before your question. In France, that small greeting often makes station, hotel, and cafe interactions smoother.",
      "Keep transport phrases ready for SNCF counters, platform changes, and train delays because rail terminology comes up quickly.",
      "Dining phrases help with set menus, allergies, and asking for the bill, especially in cafes and smaller restaurants where service feels more paced."
    ],
    "zh-CN": [
      "在法国先说一句 bonjour 再提问很重要，火车站、酒店和咖啡馆里都能明显提升沟通顺畅度。",
      "SNCF 柜台、站台变更和火车延误很常见，交通类短语最好提前准备好。",
      "餐饮短语尤其适合点套餐、说明过敏，以及在咖啡馆或小餐厅里礼貌地要账单。"
    ]
  },
  "highlights": {
    "en-US": [
      "SNCF and cafe etiquette",
      "Bakeries, menus, and museums",
      "Hotels, payments, and short service questions"
    ],
    "zh-CN": [
      "SNCF 与咖啡馆礼貌表达",
      "面包店、菜单与博物馆沟通",
      "酒店、支付与简短服务询问"
    ]
  },
